# Project Skills Reference

When working in this repo, read and follow the guidance in the `skills/` folder. These files are the source of truth for domain, architecture, and constraints.

## Skills to apply

- **Human–agent workflow** — `.cursor/rules/collaboration_workflow.mdc`  
  Spec before code, one bounded task, list files before edits, data-model assumptions before persistence, test plan + manual QA per change, diff-first for auth/db/sync/privacy, separate prompts for implement / cleanup / verify; agent calls out if steps are skipped.

- **Product and planning (no code yet)** — `skills/product_planning_well_within.md`  
  **Reference when the user is shaping features, requirements, UX/engine boundaries, acceptance criteria, or tickets before implementation.** BA + product engineer + planner role; output format and guardrails. Complements collaboration workflow (which expects a spec); does not replace domain, rules engine, or UX tone skills.

- **Fertility logic and wording** — `skills/fertility_charting_domain.md`  
  Use only observable, deterministic rules. No prediction, ML, or proprietary branding.

- **Rules engine** — `skills/rules_engine_architecture.md`  
  Core logic lives in `core/rulesEngine`. Pure functions only; no UI, storage, or network.

- **Mobile app** — `skills/mobile_app_architecture.md`  
  Thin UI; React Native + Expo + TypeScript; stack nav and local state for MVP.

- **UX tone and voice** — `skills/ux_tone_well_within.md`  
  **Reference whenever doing UX, copy, layouts, or visual design.** Calm, warm, observational tone; soft spacing and hierarchy; human language; avoid clinical or mechanical feel.

- **UX** — `skills/ux_charting_patterns.md`  
  Fast daily entry (&lt;15s), calendar-based flow, simple charts.

- **UX visual composition (premium / art direction)** — `skills/ux_visual_composition_premium.md`  
  **Reference when hierarchy, restraint, imagery, motion, or landing-style composition matter more than component count.** Complements tone and charting skills; includes Apps + utility-copy defaults for product surfaces and Expo/RN scope notes.

- **Privacy** — `skills/privacy_and_health_data.md`  
  No ad/tracking/analytics SDKs; local-only storage for MVP; user-owned data.

- **Testing** — `skills/testing_strategy.md`  
  Rules engine: 100% coverage; every verification example in docs must have a unit test; tests run in CI.

- **App Store release** — `skills/app_store_release_best_practices.md`  
  **Reference when preparing for TestFlight or App Store submission.** Stability, privacy disclosure, data controls, versioning, assets, metadata, and avoiding misleading health claims.

- **Expo iOS release** — `skills/expo_release_commands.md`  
  **Reference when building or submitting to TestFlight.** EAS setup, `eas build --platform ios`, `eas submit --platform ios`, build number management, and release workflow. Use with the readiness checklist and App Store skill.

- **Reference-to-code UI workflow** — `skills/ui_panel_workflow.md`  
  **Reference whenever a screenshot, mockup, or visual description needs to become real UI anywhere in the app** — onboarding panels, calendar screen, entry form, history view, or any component. Covers: interpret reference → find the right file → build with color tokens → verify → iterate. Includes file map, color token table, mock data policy, and anti-patterns.

- **Onboarding image quality** — `skills/onboarding_image_quality.md`  
  Sharpness, composition, and quality standards for onboarding screens. Never use blurry or upscaled assets; reconstruct in code when possible.

- **App ad creative research** — `C:\Users\JimAugustyn\.cursor\skills\app-ad-creative-research\SKILL.md`  
  **Reference when researching Instagram or Meta ads, app marketing creative, paid social concepts, growth ideas, or ad image prompts based on the app's interface.** Understand the product first, use comparable ads for patterns rather than copying, and keep claims grounded.

- **Social performance optimizer** — `C:\Users\JimAugustyn\.cursor\skills\social-performance-optimizer\SKILL.md`  
  **Reference when reviewing published Instagram or Meta post/ad performance, interpreting metrics, improving CTR or engagement, updating creative learnings, or deciding what to post/test next.** Use real metrics when available and keep tests controlled.

- **Instagram organic publishing** — `C:\Users\JimAugustyn\.cursor\skills\instagram-organic-publishing\SKILL.md`  
  **Reference when preparing, validating, approving, publishing, or reviewing organic Instagram feed posts, carousels, Stories, Reels, captions, hashtags, CTAs, link-in-bio flows, or Composio Instagram publishing workflows for Well Within.** Requires explicit approval before anything goes live.

- **Well Within Instagram research** — `C:\Users\JimAugustyn\.cursor\skills\well-within-instagram-research\SKILL.md`  
  **Reference when researching successful Instagram posts, updating Well Within social memory, maintaining the Instagram research playbook, adding draft post tests, retiring stale trends, or deciding what organic Instagram post to create next.** Use with `docs/social/INSTAGRAM_RESEARCH_PLAYBOOK.md`, `docs/social/INSTAGRAM_MEMORY.md`, `docs/social/INSTAGRAM_EXPERIMENT_LOG.md`, and `docs/social/INSTAGRAM_DRAFT_QUEUE.md`.

- **Well Within social creative direction** — `C:\Users\JimAugustyn\.cursor\skills\well-within-social-creative-direction\SKILL.md`  
  **Reference when creating, revising, or judging Instagram visuals, carousel slides, Reel covers, lifestyle imagery, creator-style posts, or social creative direction for Well Within.** Use references and a chosen visual system before generating or exporting images; avoid generic decorative cards. For feed carousels, **lock the hook slide first** and cascade the same system to later slides; use sound judgment on stock vs illustration. See `docs/social/INSTAGRAM_POST_RUNBOOK.md` for hook-first defaults, 4–5 slide preference, and imagery notes.

Before **planning** a new feature or flow (without coding), read `skills/product_planning_well_within.md` together with any domain/UX/engine skills the topic touches.

Before changing fertility behavior, the rules engine, or mobile screens, re-read the relevant skill file(s).

Before building or editing any UI component from a visual reference (screenshot, mockup, or description), read `skills/ui_panel_workflow.md`.
